🚨Breaking News 🚨

@usedgov released the rest of the education funding to the states! The release of these funds will undoubtedly have a positive impact on the kids of West Virginia.

I’ll continue to advocate with @SenCapito for the best possible outcomes when problems like this arise!

Some wonderful news I received today – over 100 Morgantown NIOSH employees will be returning to their jobs permanently.

As I have said before: The way you tackle a problem is you freeze everything, you stop everything for a time period where you can really get your hands around it, and then make the right decisions.

@POTUS and @SecKennedy are doing just that and protecting our coal miners.

Another huge win! 

@Toyota has been an incredible business partner to our state, and I'm proud to witness their continued belief and investments in hard-working West Virginians.

America is catching on to what I've known all along— West Virginia is the best place to do business.

Under Biden we blew our own legs out by not using all of the energy this country has to offer.

We need to wake up and unleash American energy.

@POTUS is getting it done. https://t.co/QoYF3lFbrd

America has catered to other countries needs for far too long.

Mexico backing down demonstrates what a strong leader can achieve. 

@POTUS and I strongly agree: the ridiculous trade imbalances that have existed must be corrected for the benefit of the American people.

Want to congratulate both Rich Rodriguez and Tony Gibson for coming home to coach in West Virginia— we all know it’s hard to stay away from the Mountain State for too long! Wishing you both the best of luck. Keep making us proud of our roots.

@RealCoachRod
@CoachTonyGibson

We’ve been quite the dynamic duo!

Grateful for Sen. Capito and all we’ve accomplished for West Virginia over the past eight years. The future is very very bright, and I know it’s full of goodness for Almost Heaven!

@SenCapito https://t.co/SaB3P5lFhG
